HEADWORD: Hyphæ
<hw>Hy"ph⟦ae⟧</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>"yfh`</grk> a web.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The long,
branching filaments of which the mycelium (and the greater part of the
plant) of a fungus is formed. They are also found enveloping the gonidia
of lichens, making up a large part of their structure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

